[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(12) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, the Chaldean.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—These words not only show that the people regarded themselves as punished by the sole hand of God, but also remind the overthrowers of the Chaldean power that they also themselves are no more than instruments of the same Divine will.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezra 5:12-14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 5:12-14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "After that our fathers had provoked the God of heaven — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It was to punish us for our sins, that we were, for a time, put out of the possession of this house, and not because the gods of the nations had prevailed against our God. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But in the first year of Cyrus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — We have the royal decree of Cyrus to justify us, and bear us out in what we do. And he not only permitted, but charged and commanded us, to build this house, and to build it ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in its place, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 5:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) the same place where it had stood before. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And the vessels also, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — These also he delivered to one whom he intrusted with the care of them, and commanded him to restore them to their ancient place and use. And these we have to show in confirmation of what we allege.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
